Patch Set 6:

This does not fail locally. I think the problem is that when single-store is in use, the test workers all share the same /tmp/staging area. If two tests that stage an image run concurrently, one will clean up the images that it doesn't know about from the other worker. AFAICT, the functional stuff doesn't let us override that conf option, so I'll have to extend it so that we can. The multistore tests use self.test_dir for staging, so they're isolated.
